content.message: Do you know much about book banning in schools?
I know a little. I know banning those two books would cost me two of my favorite books.
Are either of your favorite books "To Kill a Mockingbird" or "Huckleberry Finn"? Those are ones that come up often.
yes, I love them both. I named my dog Scout after To Kill a Mocking bird.
Harper Lee addressed a Virginia school board about their removal of her book, because they said it was "immoral".
She just released a new follow up to To Kill a Mockingbird.
Does it happen in the same area of the South, at the same time with the same characters?
I am not sure. I have not read it yet. Did you read those two books?
I read both "Huckleberry Finn" and "To Kill a Mockingbird" when I was in school.  My local school board didn't seem to have any problem with the N-word or other racial slurs in them.
Mine either. I wonder if the sensitivity will cause them to miss out on other things or shelter them from other areas that make a well-rounded adult (please don't infer I am encouraging racism).
i agree with Harper Lee who stated that she didn't think that racial tension problems would be solved by banishing classics.
Seems like she knows a lot about it. Seems reasonable to adovovate for your book.

Sometimes when books aren't banned a parent can request an alternative book, but personally it seem like you would miss out on the classroom discussions and learning if you are the only one reading it.
Yeah. I agree. I haven't read to kill a mockingbird in a while and will need to re-read it. After all, there are more libraries in the US than McDonalds.
And if  you don't want to read it in print form you can get it in another format, like audiobook, or you can use a device to read it as an e-book.
How would you like to wheelbarrow 32,000 books 3/4 of a mile at age 85???
I hope i have that much strength at age 85, or such devotion to donate them to a library like Gladstone did.
I know... MY 40 year old body aches when I get off the couch!
Well, you can get some media in a digital form from the library and stay on your couch if you want.
Nice. My life just got a little lazier... Not sure if that is a good thing...
If you need more stuff to do but don't have the equipment you could loan things from a library, they have library of things.
Nice... Thanks for the chat!
Good morning. Have you watched the Ethiopian celebrity chef? He's awesome.
I have. The way he is trying to combat hunger in his country is just awe inspiring.
It truly is. His Youtube channel is "Grandpa Kitchen". I think they should have him on Sesame Street, like Carol Burnett.
Im sad I missed that episode. She was a very funny lady. Lol. Did you now that Judge Judy makes 123000 per episode.
Yes she was. I saw that. It's crazy. Then again, so is the money LeBron makes.
I bet both she and lebron have got to go to pixars secret room. I just wonder what they keep in there.
I would love to visit that room. I wonder if Robin Williams ever did, aside from Aladdin, he did some work for Pixar as well.
With aladdin, Robin williams began the trend of celebrities voicing characters in animated films. He was a great man. I just love the work he did on the genie in aladdin.
I didn't care for it. I would have loved to have been Cristiano Renaldo's agent, he bought him an island for his wedding.
Wouldnt that be a crazy gift to recieve. He was also expelled from school for throwing a chair at a teacher.
I think it's awesome that he won't get a tattoo, because he couldn't give blood. Thats impressive.
That is a pretty good thing to do. Did you know that he is named after Ronald Reagan, his fathers favorite actor. Lol.
I did not. I did know about the little boy whose education he paid for, he was a tsunami survivor.
Soccer makes more than football basketball baseball golf tennis and hockey does combined. I think it is a lot more popular in other parts of the world than in the US.
I have never watched a pro game, and was surprised to learn that we call it "soccer"' when it is really football.
Well Im sure you know who jon stewart is from the daily show. He represented the US at the pan american maccabi games in brazil all the way back in 1983.
I do not know who he is. Did they play with three teams on the field at the same time?
I think most games are played with only two teams. Although there is a variation of the games that utilizes three teams in one game.
I still find it hard to believe that it is the world's most popular sport.
Yeah me too a little bit, until you take into account that it is played by 250 million players in over 200 countries around the world. Then it makes sense.
That's insane. I have to get to work, thanks for chatting with me. have a wonderful day.
Do you like football?
Not too much, I do not know the team names and such but watch it for fun sometimes with friends. How about you?

I am not really into football though I went to an awesome superbowl party. I didn't really pay attention tot eh game, ha. Apparently there was a University of Georgia game that had a lot of surprising comparisons to the Atlanta Falcons.
Yeah, I guess there are a lot of people who enjoy the parties that come along with the sport. There was a fun game where Georgia tech beat cumberland 222-0.
It's surprising how much the sport has evolved since then. ESPN won an emmy for the superimposed yellow line they created.
Yeah, pretty cool. I found out that the Universiry of Iowa locker room is painted pink
Yeah, I guess that was supposed to be insulting? But now pink is a color proudly worn by man NFL players in order to support the fight against breast cancer.
There you go :). Do you watch much TV, like movies and shows?

I have been watching Marvel's The Punisher lately. I think I like him because he doesn't have any really unrealistic powers like Spider Man does. The US military is actually trying to develop spiderman like abilities in their soldiers, though, so who knows if someday those powers will be a reality.

I would not be surprised at all with anything really. There is so much going on in the world and the development of new things is just crazy. Apparently Stan Lee officiated a wedding in 1987 when spiderman married mary jane where actors dressed up in costumes participated in it
Interesting! In the Amazing Spider Man comic's last issue, Doctor Octopus swaps consciousness with spiderman and becomes the new spiderman in the superior spider man series. How confusing!
I know, Spider-man seems to have really evolved over time, as many other comics really. The animated series of 1900's spiderman was performed by joe perry of aerosmith, of all people.

You mentioned Stan Lee earlier. He was supposed to get 10 percent of net profits from his characteres but for the first spider man movie the producers claimed they didn't make a profit and he got nothing.
That is just not fair. I mean Stan Lee made a great career but the beginnings are always so important. Crazy to think that Spiderman has already 10 live action movies.
Yeah, with 800 billion in revenue I doubt they were telling the truth.
Do you have a favorite player when it comes to football, as in the position they play in, quarterback, etc?
Sorry, I meant 800 million. No, I do not have a favorite, why do you ask?

Just out of curiosity. Alex Smith the quarterback took so many ap tests in high school that he entered college a a junior. Way to go for him, got a masters degree before he was even picked in the nfl draft.
Wow, that's really smart. It's a good idea to have a backup plan. Once, Baker Mayfield was going to quit football in order to become a competitive gamer.
Most definitely, I heard of a nfl player who teacher when it is not game season. Kellan Moore on the other hand is the only left handed quarterback in nfl.
It seems Tom Brady was almost prevented from advancing in football. His high school team was doing badly but refused to start him. He was backup quarterback.
Hello. Do you use Google much? A single Google search is so powerful!
I love Google, it is the #1 search engine, how about you
Yes I love it too. I mention that it was a powerful search engine. A single search requires more computing power than it took to send Neil Armstrong to the moon.
That is so crazy to think how far technology has come. I click enter in Google and I have more power than that!
It really has come along way. Google maps even tracks traffic by tracking how fast android devices are moving.
wow lol, that is awesome. Did you hear about their headquarters?
Are you referring to the fact that they haven't goats mow their lawn instead of people LOL?
right, you think they would help the economy more and hire a lawn crew or something lol
Yes good point. They have so much traffic on their site. In 2013 Google went down for about five minutes and took 40% of web traffic with it.
wow, I bet that is true! What do you think of their self driving cars?
I think they are fascinating and likely the future. Nevada thinks so too because they're the first state to allow self driving cars.
wow, I think it is scary allow AI to drive for me, but I think it will be the future of cars in my opinion
YesIt will free up a lot of time I hope. Mercedes-Benz creative self driving car in the 80s. I thought it was more of a recent thing.
Wow, I never knew that. I am one of the 75% of people who are scared of self driving cars, are you?
That is a lot of people. I think I am in the minority and I am not scared by them. I am more excited by them.
that is awesome, I think that number will change more and more they become popular. It will be like cell phones probably, you need to have one eventually
Yeah I am definitely looking forward to getting ones in the future. It would almost be like living in a video game. Speaking of video games they used to be called cathode ray tube amusement devices.
Video games sounds much better, lol! I love video games!
No doubt about that I do too. A lot of people do actually, as a planet we play 3 billion hours of video games a week. Well I really enjoyed this chat.
I enjoyed this chat as well, time to go play cathode ray tube amusement devices! Enjoy your day!
Haha awesome! Bye!
HI, how are you?
Hello, did uou watch Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom? what are your thoughs on this movie
I did not see it. Did you?
I did, I  liked it but there are some absurb scenes that didnt make sense at all
Was that the second one with Chris Pratt? I saw the first one, not the second one.
Yeah exactly thats the one with Pratt, he is a velociraptor trainer in the movie
I think I only saw that becuase my wife has a crush on him. I think he may have been shirtless on the trailer so my wife was all in on the movie. Did you like it?
I liked it, I thought it was a nice movie although many parts were unreal like when the volcano explodes and he suddenly can move again.
Ill check it out when it comes to Netflix... I found it odd that the dinosaurs were only on the screen for 15 minutes. Must have had a small CGI budget.
Yeah, Im guessing its a expensive production overall, theres a cool fact and theyy used elephant roars for the t-rex
Really? I recently heard that dinosaurs had really small and meek roars. Not at all like what is projected at movies or on TV.
Maybe they projected it this way so that they would sound scarier, also velociraptors were smaller than projected in movies.
Did you see that the park ride cost more than the movie to make?
No I actually didnt see that, os are you a dinarour fan? I used to love them when I was a little kid
I really did not get into them. That and space were never really that intriguing to me. What about you?
I like them, I  think there are many interesting facts about them I heard scientists recovered a sample of tissue and blood vessels from a T-Rex
Really! Wow, I wonder if they are going to try and clone it. Seems like something we would do and then immediately regret...
Yeah, Jurassic Park should work as a warning lol, that would definetely chage things.
I can see them screwing it up and having some sad creature that only semi-resembles a dinosaur. It would be an ethical dilema for sure.
For sure, it would generate a lot of dispute so anyway do you like how Chris Pratt acts?
I do know some like he worked at Bubba Gump. Nice chatting with you!
Are you an avid reader of comic books?
A little. I have read a few of the Marvel comics.
I know that people call them "graphic novels" now. The story lines have become more serious. I don't know how I would go about picking the best books of the year.
Comics go back as far as the 1830s and started in Japan
Really? I didn't know that. I imagine that pictorial story telling went back to the Egyptians.
Comics actually started  out as strips in newspapers in this country
The name is a bit misleading because many of the stories are quite serious. I heard that Stan Lee ends his converstaions with the word "Excelsior!" I wonder what that's about.
Stan Lee will forever be remembered. His passing was a great loss to the comic world
I heard that he got $1 million per year just to stay alive! That's a great incentive. I heard that Marvel trademarked the names super-hero and super villain.
I am just glad that Michael Jackson didn't get his hands on Marvel, he would have likely ruined it
Disney has made a lot of movies, which is good, but I wonder how the fans feel about Marvel now. Do you read DC comics ever?
Only for the Superman comic
DC stands for detective comics, so DC Comics stands for detective comics comics. I think Marvel is more popular in general.
I always found it interesting that Google got its domain from Garfield
I didn't know that! Garfield?! I think it is one of the boring-est comics out there. Lasagna + Mondays = humor? Not to me!
I was a huge Garfield fan when I was a kid
Comics are a good way for kids to learn to read. I liked reading Peanuts.
I wish I had a copy of the first comic, Famous Funnies. That is worth a lot of money I bet
I bet! I wonder what was in it. Famous Funnies, but I have no idea what characters where in there. No so famous now, I guess.
I wonder what the early Japanese comics were like?
Probably different from today's. Maybe based on samurai and ninja, not cutesy characters.
I don't think I would find them too funny either
LOL! I agree. Maybe people didn't see the medium as inherently funny. Might have watched live entertainment for laughs.
I enjoyed our conversation about comics. Thanks
hey there what do you think of planet earth?
It's a nice place. I've lived there my whole life. I'm pretty attached. What about you?
haha ya me too, sad to think that 80% of the natural forests have been destroyed though
Only 20% more to go! We are a destructive species. Can seem to protect things that we need to survive. And we've been here just a short time.
thats true, if history were a 24 hour day, humans have only taken up about 1 minute of time
The day has been getting longer. It was only 5.5 hours. Soon it'll be so long that we'll have a 20-hour workday. I bet people will want more vacation.
that is wacky, will the day continue to get longer? like a 40 hour day at somepoint?
Maybe in billions of years. Humanity will be long gone, having cut down all the forests and filled the oceans with plastic.
ya that is sad to think about, also sad we'll have run out of helium by the year 2100
We'll get our helium from fusion reactors. Every kid can have party balloons.
haha well I hope so. It's pretty silly there is an ambassador to extraterrestrials at the UN, I want his job
I think you have to know somebody. It sounds like it involves few duties. Mostly waiting.
haha ya, lots of waiting and doing nothihng, have you ever ridden a horse
Nope, never ridden a horse. Haven't eaten one either.
haha nope I have ridden one, I guess they evolved over like 50 million years
They went from multi-toed to single-toed. I guess they were more useful to humans that way.
ya I think so, they became really widespread about 3000BC, so kind of a long time
Interspecies utility is interesting. Dalmatians are associated with firefighting because they would calm  the horses.
that's nice of them. did you knw clint eastwood was allergic to horses?
Yeah, he acquired an allergy later in life. Very odd.
would you ride a horse to school?
Do you play video games?

You know, I'm older. I actually played Pong when it came out and Pacman, but I haven't in 30 years. Do you play, much experience in them? Shocking to me that Jane McGonigal calculated we play 3 billion hours of video games a week as a planet.
Interesting. I've played pong, my first game system was an Atari.
I read somewhere that Atari had 52 or 64 colors, Pong had two on my the old TV my dad had in the basement. Low tech indeed, have you played Fortnite? Seems like a big deal in gamer circles.
I think it was nintendo. I've never played Fortnite, I don't even know what it is to be honest.

Well that makes two of us, those players probably don't know what pong is/was. I have heard of Minecraft, once again never played. A world bigger than Neptune it's reported, are you familiar with that at all?
Interesting, how is that possible?
I have no idea, I assume you use Amazon though. You see where Jeff Bezos built a clock into a mountain to run 10,000 years. We'll not see that one run out of winding or battery, nor our grandkids.
I use amazon too. Do you know if it is an atomic clock?

I assume it is, I don't think we have battery technology for 10.000 years, if we did you'd never have to charge an electric car and it would run your whole life. Jeff Bezos had some problems with the National Inquirer recently, he might have wanted to hide in his warehouse. You see the workers walks 7-15 miles a day, they wouldn't need a gym membership.
yeah, I don't think so either. I didn't know that Amazon owned IMDB.

Yes, kind of makes sense if they're selling movies and video's. you see that first Amazon customer spent $27.95 in  1994 and got a building named after him. I didn't know that, had you heard that or know his/her name?
I'm not sure, I've never heard of this. I know amazon gets a special deal with the USPS.

Yes, I assume bulk savings as they might be the USPS biggest customer. It makes sense to me, you see where the first video games were called, "cathode ray tube amusement devices" and used by the military. I assume flight simulator or night goggle vision fighting, something like. You think they had any idea it would be the start of a $74 billion dollar industry worldwide?
I'm not sure. I wonder if we could get a similar USPS deal?

I really doubt it unless you ship a lot more things than I do. you see where it's illeagle for kids under 16 to play video games in South Korea after midnight, that a good idea, especially on school nights but how would the government enforce that (seems like parents should know that already and want their young kids asleep at midnight)?
Apparently as a planet we play 3 billion hours of video games a week.

Yes, and since I play none there's a few out there playing a lot to run the total up. You see where Amazon is the third most valuable company in the US by market capitilization. I mean they make some electronic devices, they really just ship goods from manufacturers to consumers. I don't think its good that they're so valuable as simply a shipping firm.
I didn't know that Jim Hanks does Woody's voice in video games, did you?
Neither did I, you think the Hanks family sits around the table at Thanksgiving using their various movie voices? That is pretty amazing family, but Tom seems like a pretty normal guy.
They seem like they would be cool people to get to know.
Hi. What kind of telephone do you have?
Well I mostly use a cellphone. I don't even have a house phone anymore, what about you
IPhone, the device famous for it's computing power! It has more CP than the entire US nuclear IBCM arsenal!
That's amazing! Scary too, do you know why New York's area code is two-one-two?
Because it is the fastest to dial on a rotary phone.  You remember rotary phones don't you?
Haha I do, I think my grandma still has one actually, she also still has phone books, have you ever interlaced all the pages of two phone books before?
No. That would take forever!  WHy, what happens?
Well once all of the pages are interlaced you literally cannot rip the two books apart, the friction keeps them together

That's hard to believe! You know what else is hard to believe?  UNICEF will donate 1 day worth of clean water to a needy child for every minute you do NOT use your cellphone.  That means you can provide clean water to 1440 children just by NOT using your cell phone!.
That sounds cool I should actually do that, I certainly don't use my phone all day, what do you think about computers by the way?

I am a computer. Well, maybe not, but I sit next to one... My computer has more RAM than I do.  But this does not bother me because it only take 1mb or RAM to run the space shuttle, and all I need to do is get to the refrigerator.
Yes that is impressive. I also want to see the Russian computer that they created to run on water, how is that possible

I don't know. I can't figure out how transhumanists think they will download their consciousness to a memory stick.  If I tried that, I would probably end up on one of those thumb drive shaped like Scooby Do...

Haha yes I would definitely upload my brain to a computer though, hopefully you don't smoke near your iPhone though, Apple says they will deny the warranty because they consider that to be a Biohazard
I consider my Iphone to be a bio-hazard with all the microwave radiation they emit. How I long for the old days when a computer could be built out of simple Minecraft building blocks...
Yep I wish I could see how they made a computer in Minecraft, that actually sounds cool, have you ever played the game of softball by the way? I'm too lazy to play sports myself
I used to play on a modified fast-pitch softball team. Love the game. I believe the YMCA invented it...
Yes you're right. It was actually invented back in 1887, which was a long time ago, it was also an indoor game originally
Nice!  Unfortunately, the average salary of a pro softball player is only about $5k per year, so I won't be doing that anytime soon.
Yep that's not too much haha. It's interesting that the game was named softball back in 1926 though, just because they use a ball that was soft LOL it makes sense
Softballs have gotten harder over the years. Hey, nice chatting with you!
Hello do you like taylor swift?
Hey there! I can tolerate Taylor Swift, she's not my favorite or anything, what about you? Did you know that she'll walk backwards so that her picture can't be taken by paparazzi?
I like her music,  I dont know much about her.  That is pretty funny and probably effective!
Yeah I could see it being effective. Do you know who Olaf the snowman is? The one from the movie Frozen? I guess she dressed up as him on tour haha that's pretty funny
wow thats awesome,  Yes I love Olaf lol Taylor swift accidently released 8 seconds of white noise and topped the canada charts lol
Haha that's funny. That's some really expensive White Noise LOL. I guess that she came from a wealthy family too, she lived on a tree farm that was about 11 acres in size
wow,  must be nice!
She does seem like she's a giver though, all the proceeds from her tour called Wildest Dream to an African Wildlife Conservation Center
Yeah Ive heard of her donating to a lot of charities and even others in need.  she gave Kesha money to fight her sexual harrassment case too.
Well that's nice of her. Does a lot of pop crossovers too, which is cool. It's also impressive that she started her music career at the age of 14.
Taylor swift removed her music from spotify because " music shouldnt be free"
That's interesting. You like her song that's called"our song"? Apparently she was the youngest person to write and perform a number one country hit, with that song,
No I havent heard of that one,  is it good?
No I haven't either. I'm not a massive fan of hers, but she does seem very talented so I'll have to check some of her stuff out. Do you like any other albums? Not necessarily by her
Yes absolutely,  my favorite right now is Bryce Vine.  I hear linkin parks album hybrid theory is the best selling of the 21st century.

Ok I'll have to check that out. What do you think about Aerosmith? Apparently they need more money by lending their rights to the Guitar Hero franchise then buy any kind of record sales LOL that's crazy
I think that was a great idea in my opinion, guitar hero was a hit because of their contribution,  thats a lot of royalties.

Yes I agree! I love playing those games when I was in high school, do you like Led Zeppelin by the way? I love that they didn't name their fourth album just to mess with the rock press, wish they hated
I never really listened to their music.  Thats hilarious.
You should check them out, they're actually really good! Just don't buy any records at Walmart by the way, they only sell clean versions of records, that would really annoy me
Yeah that is annoying, I wanna hear the music the artist released,  not some edited version.
Hi, how are you?
Good! Did you know Kristen Stewart from the Twilight movies helped author a paper about AI? Not just a pretty face!
Wow, I had no idea! That's pretty cool. Isn't that one lady from Bri bang also like a pHd?
I'm not sure but wouldn't doubt it. Facebook is developing AI designed to better understand emotions, identify objects, and predict user actions. Yikes.
Clifford seems to be a great way to augment teaching. I would like to see a pre and post test with a control group to see how well the AI works.
Interesting. At Stanford they use Google Hangouts to teach AI more effectively.
That's interesting. I teach college courses and would love to see how that works. I wonder if the non-for-profit has more info on it.
Good question. How about this one -- there's a NASA scientist who believes our world is just a computer generated VR. Maybe he's been watching too much of The Matrix.
That's nuts. I sometimes wonder if the ultra-intelligent need things to maintain their sanity...
Haha. Definitely. Overthinking can be a torture, I'm sure. The first Virtual Reality game was created in 1968. How far we've come!
I would love to go on Lockheed Martin's virtual reality tour of mars. seems like it would be a lot of fun.
It does sound fun. Up to 40% of VR users get motion sickness -- me included. So make sure to take your barf bag if you go, just in case.

I never thought of that impact on people. Have you ever gone on 4D rides at like disney? They move and shake but then they also spray water on you for when you go through water tunnels or something like that. Pretty fun.
Yeah, I took my daughter on the Stitch ride and she FREAKED OUT! She thought it was real. I felt so bad. But that's proof that 4D can ramp up the experience.
HA! How old is she? My 7 year old went on a roller coaster for the first time and freak out until the end and then I could not get him off the rides.

She was 11. But she has a really active imaginations and she loves Stitch -- so I think a part of her wanted it to be real. Wonder how she would do on that Lockheed Martin VR space bus you mentioned earlier?
I am sure she would do great! Are you on Facebook?
Yes, I'm on FB. Used to be on MySpace too, which offered to buy FB for $75 M in 2005. That would have been the buy of the century.
I know! Wht dopes! Like Iceland rewritting its constituion using ti.
There's a German state where it's illegal to use the "like" button on Facebook. Wonder what's that all about?
Nice chatting with you!
Are you a fan of soccer?
Yes. The foot ball world cup simply called as FIFA world cup. It is international competition contested by the senior men's team.
Yes!  The city which is set to host the 2022 Qatar FIFA world cup final does not exist yet.  How does that work?
The 21 world cup tournaments were won 8 teams. The world cup is most prestigious  tournament in the world. All the nation in the world want to lift the FIFA trophy.
Yes!  The Hungary national team only had 1 defeat between 1950 and 1956 and that was the world cup final!  What are the odds?
US got 3rd place in the first FIFA world cup in 1930. The american team has never placed below third place in the world cup since women world cup started in 1991 !
I'm betting on third place finishes from now on.  lol Did you know that there are no net economic gains for the countries that have played hosted to the olympics or the world cup?
Already 17 countries hosted the football world cup, Qatar has planned to hosts 2022 finals, 2026 will jointly hosted by Canada, US and Mexico.
Nice!  The current champion is France, who won on the 2018 FIFA world cup on July 15th.
After 1908 summer olympics in London football became official competitions.
I didn't know that.  At the 2014 world cup, there were more French born players playing against France than for it.
It is very sad. Very different to handle this situation.

lol  If the Algerian team had beaten Germany in their last world cup game, they would have gone on to play France on the exact date of the French invasion of Algeria's capital on July 4, 1830.  Ironic.
German goalkeeper Harald Schumacher collided with french defender patrick battiston in the 1982 world cup semifinal, All the player are very aggressive to win the trophy for the nation.
Wow!  Did you know that soccer makes more money that football, basketball, baseball, golf, tennis, and hockey combined?
Yeah. It has record of highest attendance to watch the game.
Nice.  Americans call it soccer because it was slang for association football!
Soccer is a team sport played with a spherical ball between two team of eleven players.
Did you hear of the soccer variation where 3 teams face each other at the same time?  It's been fun chatting.
Yeah. Very nice chatting with you. Have a great day.
You have a great day too!
hi how are you? have you seen guardians of the galaxy?
Hello, yes I have seen it ,  love that movie!
i have not seen it yet. i hear that it is pretty funny. i dont usually watch superhero films because it is just a lot of explosions. i like dialog.
Ah they have some pretty funny content.  I think its on Netflix right now.  Vhina/ taiwan renamed the movie to "interplanetary unusual attack team"
What the heck kind of name is that? sounds a bit stilted.
It doesnt roll off the tongue at all lol its ridiculous,  you cant even say it fast.
Yeah. Chris Pratt is in GotG, right? he is a funny guy.
Yeah he is one of the main characters,  hes is very funny in both of the movies.
He used to work at a restaurant in hawaii, i think. i saw pictures of him.
Oh really,  wow that must have been awhile ago. James gnn wanted chris pratt for the part he was willing to cgi a six pack on the actor lol
I think that is funny. chris pratt was also in a jurassic park movie. i would not have expected him to get that part.
yeah i liked him in Jurassic park too! He stole his outfit from guardians of the galaxy to visit sick children.  Guess he is following johnny depps move
Yeah, Johnny likes to go to hospitals in the Jack Sparrow outfit. great guy. the kids must love him.
Yeah that is awesome
Do you follow disney at all? i did when i was a kid.
Yes,  I actually love Disney,  My kids cant get enough of it,  I get sucked in too.
I havent seen a disney film in a while. do you have a recommendation?
Wreck it Ralph is really good.  Incredibles,  Moana,  Coco,  Frozen.  The pixar / Disney movies are really good,  but they usually dont have many or any songs.
I like the songs! they are fun, and usually well written. Anyway, great chat!
Been great chatting.
Have a great evening! Take care!
Thanks you too!
hi, do you enjoy reading?
Yes, I like to read before I go to sleep.
nice, me too. did you ever read the starship trooper?
I never read the star ship Trooper but I do like science fiction novels. It is not my first choice for a genera but I enjoy all fantasy.
yeah , me either but is it in the reading list of three out of five us military branches

All processed foods are out.  I have been successful with weight loss on it before.
